<Issue id="28290" key="CE-294" number="294" project="10200" reporter="tongliofcary" assignee="tongliofcary" creator="tongliofcary" type="10004" summary="k8s now requires fail-swap-on to be set to false" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="10001" created="2018-03-08 03:39:01.0" updated="2018-03-09 03:57:42.0" resolutiondate="2018-03-09 03:57:32.0" votes="0" watches="2" workflowId="28293"> <description><! CDATA k8s fails kubelet if your system swap flag is on. Kubelet won't fail in the past but now if the swap is on from your operating system, kubelet will fail to start. The solution is to set that kubelet flag fail-swap-on to false. Then kubelet will work appropriately. but the real solution is to set the system swap off like using this command   sudo swapoff -a  ></description> </Issue>
